<span id="freeTextContainer2608891103816554905">I&apos;m torn with this book. On the one hand the prose is so dense and rich, poetic and downright stunning. On the other hand the story left me a little hollow. Reading this I had the perpetual feeling that I was trying to see through a foggy window, barely seeing. And yet, there was so much feeling. <br/><br/>Characters appear as if in a dream and dissolve away. Frustrating? Yes. But isn&apos;t that how life is? People leave. People die. And we feel the loss forever, as the characters in this book do. <br/><br/>I&apos;m not sur</span>
  <span id="freeText2608891103816554905" style="display:none">I'm torn with this book. On the one hand the prose is so dense and rich, poetic and downright stunning. On the other hand the story left me a little hollow. Reading this I had the perpetual feeling that I was trying to see through a foggy window, barely seeing. And yet, there was so much feeling. <br /><br />Characters appear as if in a dream and dissolve away. Frustrating? Yes. But isn't that how life is? People leave. People die. And we feel the loss forever, as the characters in this book do. <br /><br />I'm not surprised to learn the author is a poet. This book reads like a dream. There was just a little <i>something</i> missing.</span>
